Heat oven to 375 degrees F. Make broccoli with cheese sauce as directed on package. Heat oil in 10-inch nonstick skillet over medium heat. Cook bell pepper, garlic and onion in oil 2 minutes. Stir in beans; cook 1 minute. Stir in cilantro and jalapeno pepper. Remove from heat. Divide and spread bean mixture evenly over each of 4 tortillas. Top each with broccoli and cheese. Top each with 1 tortilla. Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake about 10 minutes or until hot. Cut into wedges; serve with salsa.